nd institutions. She traces efforts to remake village education, economics, and politics, analyzing how these efforts contributed to a new, inclusive vision of rural Chinese life. Merkel-Hess argues that as China sought to redefine itself, such rural reform efforts played a major role, and tensions that emerged between rural and urban ways deeply informed social relations, government policies, and subsequent efforts to create a modern nation during the communist period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEducation, RuralxHistoryx20th centuryxChina. 0aEducation, RuralzChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aRural developmentxHistoryx20th centuryxChina. 0aRural developmentzChinaxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aChina.  aCommunists.  aRural Reconstruction Movement.  acountryside.  aliteracy.  amodernity.  arural cosmopolitanism.  arural reconstruction.  aself government.  avillage.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022638327940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226383309423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226383309/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles